To Robert VVilde, D.D. in the words of his own poem, concerning Mr. Edmond Calamy.
1 sheet ([1] p.).
s.n.], [S.l. : Printed anno Domini. 1662.
Verse: "This Page I send to you Sir, your Gouty Fate ..." In response to Robert Wild's A poem upon the imprisonment of Mr. Calamy in Newgate. Cf. Wing T1384A, which has "poem on Mr. Edmond Calamy" in title. Reproduction of original in the British Library.
